{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Manually crafted prompts [224]- [227], [229], [235], [253], [267] are designed to guide a pre-trained model to align with downstream tasks.",
    "Especially, regarding the design principles of prompts, BFSPR [235] discovered that a more detailed prompt design can enhance performance, and thus it used various combinations from a small category set to explore diverse settings.",
    "Qin et al. [269] also showed that using essential attributes, such as color, shape, and location, can enhance domain transfer capability compared to the default category names.",
    "Besides, Guo et al. [270] utilized multiple prompts fusion to comprehensively describe information about recognized objects.",
    "Xplainer [268] presented prompts that are initially generated using ChatGPT and then refined with a seasoned radiologist for better performance."
  ],
